Character is Alphabet or Not
Write a C program to check whether a character is alphabet or not.
Sample Input
Sample input  : char ch = 'A
Sample input  : char ch = '9';

Sample Output
Sample output : Alphabet
Sample output : Not Alphabet



#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    char ch;
    // char ch2;
    scanf("%c", &ch);
    // scanf("%c", &ch2);

    if((ch >= 65 && ch<=90) || ch >= 97 && ch<=122){
        printf("%c is Alphabet",ch);
    }else{
        printf("%c Is Not Alphabet", ch);
    }
}



/////////////////////////////////////////////



ConvertAlphabet
Write a C program to convert Character
  (Upper to Lower or Lower to Upper).
Sample Input
Sample input  : char ch ='A'
Sample input  : char ch = 'b';
Sample Output
Sample output : a
Sample output : B



#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    char ch;
    scanf("%c", &ch);

    if(ch>=65 && ch<=90){
        printf("%c",ch+32);
    }else{
        printf("%c", ch-32);
    }
}


