PassOrFail
Write a C program that takes the marks of a student in three subjects as input and prints whether the student has passed or failed in three subject using  if statement.
	if marks is above 35 then pass and student is fail in any one subject then fail.


Sample input  :  
		Enter three subject marks : 57 66 88
Sample output : 
		Result is pass 

Sample input  :  
		Enter three subject marks : 71 64 32
Sample output : 
		Result is Fail
Sample Input
57
66
88
Sample Output
Result is pass



#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    int marks1;
    int marks2;
    int marks3;

    scanf("%d%d%d",&marks1,&marks3,&marks3);
    if(marks1 > 35 && marks2>35 && marks3 > 35){
        printf("Result is pass");
    }else{
        printf("Result is Fail");
    }
}


/////////////////////////////////////


MaxBetweenThree
Write a C program to find maximum between three numbers.

Sample input  : int a = 100, b = 200, c = 300
Sample output : 300
Sample Input
100 200 300
Sample Output
300



#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    int a,b,c;
    scanf("%d%d%d",&a,&b,&c);

    if(a>=b && a>=c){
        printf("%d", a);
        return 0;
    }
    if(b>=a && b>=c){
        printf("%d",b);
        return 0;
    }
    if(c>=a && c>=b){
        printf("%d",c);
        return 0;
    }
}


